reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for Packing!
reviews.reviewText: We travelled to Italy with only a carry on suitcase and I used these to optimize the little space I had. They came in very handy and performed well. A few times I overpacked them and the zippers took the tension well. The compression comes in handy when you don't have a lot of space but I've also used them several times just for organization while traveling and not necessarily needing the compression. The beige is nice and matched with everything. I will not be traveling without these! would purchase these again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All the things...
reviews.reviewText: This compression set is amazing. It has all the sizes that you need to pack for a 7 night trip. It's durable, easy to pull the zippers to do the compressing and fits tons of stuff. I travel a lot and really like this set. The only negative is that the dirty laundry bag isn't really big enough to hold dirty clothes, but makes a perfect sized bag to throw a few pair of shoes into. It's a great value, at least at the price I paid.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absolute game changer for travel organization!
reviews.reviewText: I LOVE packing cubes and these are even better since they can compress! Now I can organize all my goodies perfectly and save space with bulky / nonstandard type clothing (sweaters, jackets, etc).Pros:- many size options- easy to use compressed and uncompressed- comes with bags that can be used to separate dirty laundry- nice, easy to clean materialCons:- Can be difficult to gauge how much to fill a bag to ensure compression can still occur

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Useful but not perfect
reviews.reviewText: Overall, I'm glad I bought these for a recent trip overseas. They kept my clothes organized and did provide a bit more room in the suitcase. But, one of the zippers broke almost immediately (I may have over stuffed the cube). And I would say the compression is moderate, not huge. However, I did also use some of those "true compression" plastic packing bags, and those were a bit more hard, blocky, and awkward to fit in the suitcase. So in the end I preferred these even though the compression wasn't as good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Packing game changer
reviews.reviewText: Packing is now much more organized within my carryon-shirts, socks, pants, etc can be grouped together and I know where they all go in which cube when I need to repack at the end of my trip. I am also not worried if for some reason I have to open my carryon during tsa inspections-I know that everything will fit, strangers won’t be looking at my clothes and it will quickly and neatly go back in the case without loosing anything. These particular cubes seem decent they have so far held up on three different long trips so far where I have stuffed them to the hilt. No sign of wear and tear yet-I can tell they should last me for at least a couple of years of regular traveling. I have a history of overpacking so these were a game changer for me-you must be decisive of what you bring-a suitcase can only hold so much and since these cubes compress my clothes, I can still bring that extra sweatshirt for just in case. I really like these and the dark color matches my suitcase. You can slightly see through the mesh which I like so you can tell slightly what you put in there and there is one blacked out one for unmentionables-again which is great-I can’t stand having my underwear jumbled up in my regular clothes-especially when traveling with others. My biggest advice when trying to get more clothes in a cube than you probably should-is to go slow when zipping them up. It will take a bit of time and you might need to use your body weight and a bit of finagling to help compress them. I have tried rolling vs folding shirts and it doesn’t make a difference. Just go slow and they work fantastic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight and packs easily
reviews.reviewText: Ordered these for a trip, and they did the job. Definitely keeps your things organized and separate. I used a bag towards the end for dirty clothes which was helpful. I don’t think they’ll last forever but at the price point, you can’t go wrong.
